Here's how to handle each scenario in MSTest:

### 1. Windows-only (registry)
```csharp
[TestMethod]
public void ReadRegistryKey()
{
    if (!RuntimeInformation.IsOSPlatform(OSPlatform.Windows))
        Assert.Inconclusive("Requires Windows.");

    // registry test logic...
}
```

### 2. Skip in CI (requires GPU)
```csharp
[TestMethod]
public void RenderWithGpu()
{
    if (Environment.GetEnvironmentVariable("CI") == "true")
        Assert.Inconclusive("Requires a local GPU; skipped in CI.");

    // GPU test logic...
}
```

Or use **categories** and exclude at the runner level:
```csharp
[TestMethod]
[TestCategory("RequiresGPU")]
public void RenderWithGpu() { /* ... */ }
```
```bash
dotnet test --filter "TestCategory!=RequiresGPU"
```

### 3. Flaky external API — use `[Retry]` (MSTest v3.4+)
```csharp
[TestMethod]
[Retry(3)]  // retries up to 3 times on failure
public async Task GetWeatherForecast()
{
    var result = await _weatherClient.GetForecastAsync("Seattle");
    Assert.IsNotNull(result);
}
```

### 4. Cleanup even on failure — use `[TestCleanup]`
```csharp
[TestClass]
public class TempFileTests
{
    private string _tempFile = null!;

    [TestInitialize]
    public void Setup()
        => _tempFile = Path.GetTempFileName();

    [TestCleanup]  // runs after EVERY test, even if it throws
    public void Cleanup()
    {
        if (File.Exists(_tempFile))
            File.Delete(_tempFile);
    }

    [TestMethod]
    public void WriteAndReadTempFile()
    {
        File.WriteAllText(_tempFile, "hello");
        Assert.AreEqual("hello", File.ReadAllText(_tempFile));
    }
}
```

**Key takeaways:**

| Scenario | Mechanism |
|---|---|
| OS-specific | `Assert.Inconclusive()` at runtime |
| Skip in CI | Environment check or `--filter TestCategory!=X` |
| Flaky/external | `[Retry(N)]` (MSTest ≥ 3.4) |
| Guaranteed cleanup | `[TestCleanup]` method |

`Assert.Inconclusive` marks the test as **skipped/warning** (not failed), so your CI stays green while clearly signaling the test didn't run.
